{"body": "Hey @al2o3cr, I particularly don't think it's AR's responsibility (or Relation) to handle wrapping to another objects. When one instantiate an Active Record object, ie with `first`, he'd expect to get back an AR instance, not a wrapped object.\n\nSo, my 2 cents are that there's no real gain baking this into Rails, when we can be explicit about the wrapping whenever necessary, with your example:\n\n```ruby\nUser.where(:name => 'Bob').wrap_with(UserWrapper).first.magic_thing\n#vs\nUserWrapper.new(User.where(:name => 'Bob').first).magic_thing\n\nUser.where(:name => 'Bob').wrap_with(UserWrapper)\n# vs\nUser.where(:name => 'Bob').map { |u| UserWrapper.new(u) }\n```\n\nThanks!", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/8283407", "created_at": "2012-09-05T00:05:06Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/7520#issuecomment-8283407", "updated_at": "2012-09-05T00:05:06Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 7520, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/carlosantoniodasilva", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://1.gravatar.com/avatar/77237b97a465ae5a293ad323b7296837?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F60b997fd68261ce70cadaf6c8226c042.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/received_events", "gravatar_id": "77237b97a465ae5a293ad323b7296837", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "carlosantoniodasilva",